			</td><td width="2%">&nbsp;</td><td width="44%"> Abstract
			<div style="text-align:justify;">
				<P>
					<B>Introduction</B>: This research is integrated in the research group of the Master´s program and Doctorate in Education - PPGE - PUCPR in Teacher Training project Teachers at Different Levels and Contexts, coordinated by Prof. Dr. Elizete L.M Matos, integrates with project approved by CNPq, entitled Lego favoring pedagogical proposals to the school in health care.
The project aims to provide the implementation of LEGO in home teaching service, along with students who are unable to attend school due to the treatment, favoring the continuation of studies in the city of Curitiba. As guaranteed by the document Hospital Classroom and Educational Service Household					<B>Objectives</B>: The project aimed to the proposition and implementation of the educational proposal with LEGO material to school in health care, in home teaching service in the city of Curitiba.
Besides taking the student PIBITI, to participate in the whole process that involves home care, therefore, essentially part of the training, with the various courses offered, which refer to the care with hygiene, it requires special care with student in health care, furthermore, the material proposed for use.					<B>Methods</B>: Research qualitative approach type action research					<B>Results</B>: The project with LEGO, is of great importance, as it is noticed to the survey, the results are positive this material provides, it offers the school the full development of their skills and monitoring of school subjects and can undoubtedly accompany the class when released by the doctor to return to the classroom.					<B>Conclusion</B>: They could be noticed most important points with the implementation of the project, which did not happen, but the training has happened effectively brought important knowledge and information, which prepared for the practical part of the research. Online courses, increased the level of depth to the research, in relation to technology and pedagogy hospital also travel on LEGO, made us know its origin, benefits and method used in its educational proposal also the course bioethics provided an opportunity to prepare for care that are essential when it involves school in health care.
As regards the proposal and implementation of LEGO, educational materials in home care to school in health care, there was no effect, as justified, but there is good acceptance by involved professionals like teachers and teachers of the University Hospital Cajuru and those involved with home teaching service, as the indigenous and residential house.				</P>
